1995 - 1938
TO THE MEMORY OF JOHN KIDBY WHO DEVOTED MUCH OF HIS
LEISURE TIME TO RESTORING THE AVRO YORK AND RECORDING
THE SOCIETY'S ACTIVITIES WITH HIS PHOTOGRAPHIC SKILLS.
REMEMBERED BY HIS MANY FRIENDS AND COLLEAGUES OF THE
DUXFORD AVIATION SOCIETY AND THE IMPERIAL WAR MUSEUM."Ω
∫He offered a welcoming smile
and contagious enthusiasm for aviation
He shared his wide knowledge and many contacts
and left a legacy of memorable anecdotes
George W Paul
